               <p>MARY 
               <persName id="t18311201-260-person1975">
                  ANN 
                  LODGE
               <interp inst="t18311201-260-person1975" type="surname" value="LODGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-260-person1975" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-260-person1975" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the prisoner's sister. I live with my mother, but not my father; the prisoner has been very much neglected by his father for the last three years, and has lived with us - I had some money in a trunk in the room the prisoner slept in, on the 24th of November; he got up that morning before seven o'clock, and went away: my sister and I had been up at work till two in the morning, and we did not get up till eight - I then missed three half-crowns, four shillings, and one sixpence of mine, and a pair of shoes of my sister's; I went and found him at the top of Golden-lane, between eight and nine o'clock the same evening.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-260-person1976">
                  EMMA 
                  LODGE
               <interp inst="t18311201-260-person1976" type="surname" value="LODGE"></interp>
